supportDesc.foliation: Modern foliation in pencil. Errors in foliation: f. 1-34, 34a, 35-123, 123a, 124-140, 140a, 141-298 (not taking into account the dummy leaves).

collation.p: The original quire structure consists of quinternions or quaternions with two singletons added. There are also several singletons (often in the form of slips) added to the quinternions. Quire 14 lacks 2 leaves and quire 16 lacks 1. After the modern rebinding dummy leaves haved been added to the singletons creating a new structure consisting mainly of sesternions. The viscoll collation shows the modern stucture with dummy leaves marked in blue. This collation is based on former librarian Anna Wolodarski's work.

collation.catchwords: Catchwords in black ink in a red scroll.

history.origin: Sweden Stockholm , 1460. Written for the chapel of Helgeandshuset (Hospital of the Holy Ghost) in Stockholm.
history.provenance: Some time after the dissolution of Helgeandshuset in 1531, the manuscript was probably transferred to Stockholm Cathedral (Storkyrkan), cf. by G.E. Klemming.
history.acquisition: Acquired from the archive of the consistory of Stockholm via J.W. Beckman on .

note.p: Canon image and most of the the Ordo and Canon missae missing because of a lost quire. The last rubric on is benediccio aque. After this a singleton and an entire quire would have followed, but these are now lost; the first rubric on is hic leuat manus sursum dicans.
